  "prompt": "Do Las Vegas Casinos pump oxygen into the air conditioning systems? Why?",
  "response": "There is a common belief that Las Vegas casinos pump oxygen into their air conditioning systems to keep patrons awake and encourage them to gamble longer. However, this is largely a myth. \n\nWhile casinos do focus on creating an environment that is comfortable and inviting, they typically do not inject extra oxygen into the air. Instead, they use sophisticated air conditioning systems to maintain a steady temperature and control humidity, as well as to ensure good air circulation. The goal is to create an atmosphere that feels pleasant and keeps patrons engaged without compromising safety or health.\n\nThe idea behind the myth may stem from the fact that casinos are often designed to feel energetic, with bright lights and engaging sounds, which can create a stimulating environment that encourages people to stay and play. Additionally, factors such as the absence of windows and clocks can contribute to a sense of timelessness that keeps gamblers inside for longer periods.",
